enhanced_by.reason: The element method operates on a SynchronizedQueue instance, which is created by the synchronizedQueue method.
The element method retrieves an element from the queue, which requires the queue to have elements. The offer method adds elements to the queue.
Both element and peek methods retrieve an element from the queue without removing it, making them functionally similar.
The remove method removes an element from the queue, which can affect the state of the queue before calling the element method.
